consent:
Purpose

This study aims to investigate perceptions of intimate partner violence. If you volunteer to participate in this research study, we will ask you to fill out questions regarding stereotypes of intimate partner violence. You will not be presented with disturbing material or information. 



Time Commitment

Your participation is expected to take about 15 minutes. 



Potential Benefits

You will not directly benefit from your participation in this study. However, this study may provide valuable information about how people perceive certain scenarios of intimate partner violence. 



Confidentiality

We will make our best efforts to maintain confidentiality of any information that is collected during this study. We will protect your confidentiality by ensuring that your name and other identifiable information are not present in the data for this study. All data will be stored on a password-protected hard drive. The research team and authorized university staff may have access to the research data. Research records provided to authorized, non-university individuals will not contain identifiable information about you. Any publications and/or presentations that result from this study will not contain any identifiable information.



Participant’s rights

Your participation in this study is voluntary and you have the right to withdraw your consent and stop your participation at any time, without any penalty. Your participation is anonymous, and your answers cannot be traced back to you.

 

Contact

Hanna Feige

Graduate Student

gusfeigha@student.gu.se
